title: Oleander--February Son--vikingsfreak
description:
February Son is the major label debut album from post-grunge band Oleander. It was released on Universal Records in 1999 and eventually went gold.

The album includes Oleander's breakout single "Why I'm Here" as well as a cover of The Cure's "Boys Don't Cry." Also, most of the songs in the album had been previously released on the band's first independent releases. February Son also includes new drummer Scott Devours. Devours was hired to replace the band's original drummer, Fred Nelson Jr.
